Blueprint Library — Django + Neon blueprint (structured knowledge + cross-reference graph)

What it is

Blueprint Library is a structured knowledge system for storing long-form entries, linking them together, tagging them, and browsing relationships. It’s not a note app — it’s a knowledge graph you can navigate. Think operator manuals, build blueprints, process docs, or conceptual frameworks.

This showcases Django strengths: relational modeling, search, graph relationships, and admin tooling.


---

Shared backbone (required in every Neon-backed Django app)

Flow: Browser → Django app → Neon Postgres

Identity

Django authentication (email/password)

All content scoped to user ownership


Server invariants

Django pinned version

ORM only (no raw SQL unless needed)

Env-based secrets only

No unnecessary logging or telemetry



---

Stack

Django

Neon Postgres

Markdown rendering (optional but recommended)

Full-text search using Postgres



---

Core concepts

This app stores Blueprint Entries that can:

• link to other entries
• belong to categories
• be tagged
• contain structured sections
• be navigated as a graph


---

Data model

BlueprintEntry

user (FK)

title

slug

summary

body (markdown/text)

created_at

updated_at


Category

user

name


Tag

user

name


EntryLink (graph edges)

from_entry

to_entry

relationship_type (e.g., “depends_on”, “expands”, “example_of”)


EntrySection (optional but powerful)

entry

heading

content

order



---

Postgres enhancements (Neon)

GIN index for search

trigram index for fuzzy title search (optional)


Indexes:

(user, slug) unique

GIN on body + summary

(from_entry, to_entry) index



